snippet.textDisplay:
This is one of my first times watching your program and I enjoyed it. My daughter is a subscriber and she often talks about you and your observations. You seem very intelligent.
I wish you didn't use the epithet "Beautiful Bastards," for your viewers. I'm not a bastard. I'm not particularly beautiful, either, but that inaccuracy is easier for me to overlook. Or are you only addressing your subscribers? Actually, I would find that even more insulting, since my daughter, who is decidedly not a bastard, is a subscriber.
I like the way you address what's going on in the world. You seem to have a fairness that I find lacking in many news sources.



I agree with the penalties given to those who seem to be actively spreading the disease. I realize that some of these people are simply being recklessly impulsive. It seems that the media these days tends to encourage outrageous behavior. For some of these individuals, the maximum penalty of the law may be too severe. Hopefully, they would end up out early for good behavior and on probation. But the severity of the penalty is needed for a deterrent, in my opinion.
